[SN]TITLE[SN]
Staff tied up in shop robbery in Claydon

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two members of staff have been tied up during a robbery at a Suffolk shop.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Three men wearing balaclavas entered a branch of the One Stop Stores on Ipswich Road, Claydon, at around 06:00 GMT.
One of the men said he had a knife and a quantity of cash was stolen.
The men are described as average build, one was black and wore a peaked cap, another had tattoos on his face, which possibly included a cross.
